  "body": "Currently, the hash policy for a route supports hashing on a header's entire value:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/api/envoy/config/route/v3/route_components.proto#L609\r\n\r\nWe have a use case in which we'd like to hash on a regex substitution on `:path` (e.g.: to extract a given id). \r\n\r\nThere's two options I can think of:\r\n\r\n1) add support for hashing on a metadata key (reusing what was added in ##11698)\r\n\r\n2) add support for applying `type.matcher.v3.RegexMatchAndSubstitute` on a header and then hashing on that result\r\n\r\nAny preferences/thoughts?\r\n\r\ncc: @htuch @snowp @mattklein123 ",
